title: Red Hawks Rippin' Road Weekend
description: The Ripon College Red Hawks Cycling Team hosts its first ever MidWest Collegiate Cycling Conference Road Race Weekend April 5, 2014. Races will be held rain or shine. HELD UNDER USA CYCLING PERMIT
course: The TTT will feature a 5-mile out-and-back course for an approximately 10-mile total run that includes a bit of climbing on quietly travelled rural roads (http://www.mapmyride.com/routes/fullscreen/374228169/). The criterium will feature a roughly 1-mile lap through a developing neighborhood (http://www.mapmyride.com/routes/fullscreen/153124111/). Not your typical flat, four-cornered crit, this course will be fast and challenging. Both the TTT and the crit will share the same Start/Finish (located near 250 Moraine Drive, Ripon, WI  54971), making for a convenient transition from event to event.
registration: Advanced Online Registration is $30 per team for the TTT and $15 per individual for the criterium. On-site registration will open at 7 a.m. Saturday and will close 15 minutes prior to race start for each category. A $5 late fee per event will be charged for onsite registration.
notes: All race times are Central Daylight Savings Time.
directions:
The TTT and criterium will share the same Start/Finish line near 250 Moraine Drive, Ripon, WI  54971. Please park on Casey Road, located off Hwy. 23/49 to the south between McDonald's and O'Reilly Auto Parts.
The race site is a stone's throw from hotels and restaurants. Comfort Suites at Royal Ridges (http://www.comfortsuites.com/hotel-ripon-wisconsin-WI133) will give a discount when you mention you are attending the Ripon College race.

title: WI State Road Championship --  Spring Prairie Road
John Hatherly Mid Century Ride - Waupaca
description: John Hatherly is an avid cyclist an recently turned 50.  As a surprise for his 50th, his wife honored him with a bike ride in his honor.  The Hatherly's have a home in Waupaca and wanted to share this ride with the community.  Multiple distance rides are available for all to enjoy.  In addition the event will provide scholarships to two graduating Waupaca High School seniors.
course:
There are multiple distances that will all begin and end at Waupaca High School.  Because of the flower-petal design of the course, you can build your own distance based on how you feel that day.  Standard distances include 12, 20, 50, 62, 70 and 100 miles.  The 100 mile course will be two loops of the 50 mile distance.
 
There will be a two rest stop locations.  The first will be at high school.  Riders will pass this rest stop at mile mile 20 and again at mile 50.  In addition, there will be a rest stop at mile 32.  100 mile riders will also see this rest stop at mile 82.

title: Red Hawks Rampage
description: The 2014 Red Hawks Rampage will include Downhill, Cross-Country, Short Track XC and the XC Relay.  Racing begins Saturday 9/21 at Nordic Mountain in Mt. Morris, WI at 11:00am.  Trails open for practice runs in the DH at 9am.
course: The 100 acres on and around the slopes of this ski area are home to one of the best cross-country courses in the midwest.  The course will be an adaptation of the previously held Subaru Cup PRO XCT courses.  Each lap will include challenging climbs, technical single track, fast descents, rock gardens and so much more!  Each lap will be approximately 5 miles in length.
registration: Race entry fee is $15 per event.  Preregister at usacycling.org.  Pre-reg closses at 11:59pm September 17th.  Onsite registrants will incur a $5 late fee.  Onsite registration closes 15 minutes before the start of each race.  Riders must have a valid USA Cycling Collegiate license.  One day license ($10) and annual license ($30) will be available for purchase onsite.
directions: GPS Address: W5806 CTY Rd. W. Wild Rose, WI 54984;  From Chicago, follow I94N to Milwaukee.  Follow 894 (bypass) around Milwaukee to US Hwy 41/45.  Follow 41 N to Oshkosh.  Take exit 119 for HWY 21 west towards Redgranite.  Once through Redgranite, turn right on Cty Rd Z.  Turn left on Cty Rd S.  Turn right on State Rd 152.  Rurn right on Cty Rd W.  Follow Cty Rd W approx 1 mile.  Nordic Mountain is on the left hand side.

title: Trek Cyclocross Collective Cup
description: Madcross Promotions LLC., with the support of Trek, our other sponsors & all of our Hard Working volunteers, are proud to present the Trek Cyclocross Collective Cup Weekend. This event promises fun and exciting racing for everyone with each day culminating with the Elite Men and Women. The amateurs will be able to race on the same course the Elite Pros will use later in the day.
course: The course is laid out primarily on the grounds of Trek’s Headquarters.  The course has varied terrain and will feature some challenging sections that will test the rider’s fitness and skill.  The terrain includes - hard packed grass, pavement, and paved parking lots and access roads.  A long starting stretch is featured, and the finish is long & straight and both are on a paved parking lot area. The course will feature plenty of twists and turns, off camber sections, steep climbs and an steep hill that may need to be run.  The Wheel/Bike Pit area offer easy access, offers two (2) sided and is located in a flat grassy area. The course is approximately 2.8 KM long/lap.  The course will remain similar, with some minor changes for Sunday.
